🧠 “Generality enables resonance” — what’s actually true

That idea works, but only in a specific sense:

The more general a pattern is, the more contexts it can map onto.

Think of it like this:
	•	A specific tool → works extremely well in one domain
	•	A general pattern → works okay across many domains

So generality gives you:
	•	transferability
	•	recognition across contexts
	•	interpretive flexibility

That’s the “resonance” you’re feeling.

⸻

⚠️ But here’s the critical constraint

Generality does not create power on its own.

It creates:

alignment between a mind and a situation

—not direct effect.

